"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-06-team-gb-star-fears-smoking-ban-will-hurt-medal-chances-paris-olympics-21373742\", \"text\": \"Team GBstar Charley Hull fears her chances of claiming gold in the women's golf event may have taken a hit due to the smoking ban in place at theParis Olympic Games.  Hull is one of few golfers who smokes while competing and went viral last month at theUSWomen's Open when she was captured signing autographs with a cigarette hanging out of her mouth.  The British No.1 was recently diagnosed with attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) and says that smoking helps her to concentrate but she will not be able to do so in Paris this week after organisers designated all venues as smoke-free zones.  Hull finished seventh at the Rio Games in 2016 but fears the ban will mess with her usual routine, affecting her chances of making the podium at Le Golf National.  Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  'I do smoke on the course. It's a habit but I will not do it this week. Yeah, just something I do. I do not think you are allowed,' she told reporters ahead of the first round on Wednesday.  'Yeah, I think it will [affect me]. Because it relaxes me a little bit. But it is what it is.'  But while Hull's smoking antics saw her gain an army of new followers on social media, the Englishwoman insists she has not paid much attention to her new cult following.  .@HullCharleymaking John Daly proud. \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u0082pic.twitter.com/hmp7EaiKRr  'I have not gone on Instagram in about four or five months,' she said. 'I do not go on social media. I just let my agent do it.'  Hull, representing Team GB alongside close friend Georgia Hall, will hope to emulate the efforts of Tommy Fleetwood who claimed a hard-fought silver in the men's event last week and said she looked forward to playing in front of a rapturous French crowd.  'I did not see it [Fleetwood winning silver] - I was actually on the golf course playing in England,' she said.  'I do not really watch much TV but my friends were showing me shots and that and I thought it was great what he did. I thought he was going to get gold at one point but I bet he's pretty happy with silver.  'I think it will be great with the crowds. It's always good to interact with the crowd and people watching. I love to play in front of crowds.  'I like being entertaining on the golf course. Yeah, I am hoping the crowds are big and a few people from England make it over the Channel.'  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:BBC presenter Gabby Logan raises doubt over Olympics bell  ArrowMORE:Simone Biles responds to NFL star calling her classy Olympic gesture 'disgusting'  ArrowMORE:'It's a scandal!' - Olympian blasts penalty for every French medallist at Paris 2024  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"